Part 1: Evaluation Overview
1. Evaluation

EN: Evaluation is the process of assessing the usability of a system or interface.
中: 评估是衡量系统或界面可用性的过程。
Example: Test a website usability / 测试网站可用性

2. Why Evaluate?

EN: Evaluation determines usability, identifies problems, compares designs, and observes user behavior.
中: 评估用于判断系统是否好用、找出问题、比较设计方案并观察用户行为。
Example: Compare two app designs / 比较两个应用

3. Importance of Evaluation

EN: Evaluation ensures users can use and like the system before release.
中: 评估确保系统在发布前能被用户使用并接受。
Example: Fix errors early / 提前修复错误

4. Goals of Evaluation

EN: To assess usability, functionality, satisfaction, and identify specific issues.
中: 评估目标是检查可用性、功能性、满意度并找出问题。
Example: Find confusing features / 找出困惑功能

5. What to Evaluate?

EN: Both early and final designs should be evaluated.
中: 早期和最终设计都需要评估。
Example: Paper prototype / 纸上原型

6. When to Evaluate?

EN: Evaluation should occur throughout the Human–Computer Interaction process.
中: 评估应贯穿整个 HCI 过程。
Example: Test at every stage / 每阶段测试

7. Where to Evaluate?

EN: Evaluation can be done in laboratories or real-world environments.
中: 可在实验室或真实环境进行评估。
Example: Usability lab / 可用性实验室

8. Types of Evaluation

Formative Evaluation: Conducted during design / 设计中评估
Summative Evaluation: Conducted after completion / 完成后评估
Example: Improve prototype vs final test / 原型改进 vs 最终测试

9. Evaluation Methods

EN: Main methods are expert analysis and user participation.
中: 主要方法是专家分析和用户参与。
Example: Expert review vs user testing / 专家评估 vs 用户测试

10. User Participation

EN: Real users perform tasks and give feedback.
中: 真实用户执行任务并提供反馈。
Example: User testing session / 用户测试

11. Laboratory Studies

EN: Users perform tasks in a controlled environment.
中: 用户在受控环境中完成任务。
Example: Screen recording / 屏幕录制

12. Field Studies

EN: Evaluation conducted in the user’s real environment.
中: 在真实使用环境中评估。
Example: Workplace observation / 工作场所观察

Part 2: Expert Analysis
13. Expert Analysis

EN: Experts evaluate usability without involving real users.
中: 专家在无真实用户参与下评估可用性。
Example: Expert reviews interface / 专家评估界面

14. Why Use Expert Analysis?

EN: Fast, low cost, suitable for early design stages.
中: 速度快、成本低，适合设计早期。
Example: Early prototype review / 早期原型评估

15. Types of Expert Analysis

EN: Includes heuristic evaluation, cognitive walkthrough, and guideline review.
中: 包括启发式评估、认知走查和准则评估。

16. Heuristic Evaluation

EN: Experts inspect interfaces using usability heuristics.
中: 专家依据可用性原则检查界面。
Example: Check feedback and consistency / 检查反馈与一致性

17. Nielsen’s Usability Heuristics

EN: Ten heuristics proposed by Jakob Nielsen.
中: Jakob Nielsen 提出的十项可用性原则。
Example: Visibility of system status / 系统状态可见性

18. Cognitive Walkthrough

EN: Step-by-step evaluation of task learnability for new users.
中: 逐步评估新手用户的可学习性。
Example: First-time task completion / 新手完成任务

19. Guideline Review

EN: Interface is compared against established guidelines or standards.
中: 将界面与设计准则或标准对比。
Example: ISO guideline check / ISO 标准检查

20. Role of Experts

EN: Identify problems, suggest improvements, guide redesign.
中: 发现问题、提出建议并指导重新设计。
Example: Usability consultant / 可用性顾问

Part 3: Usability Measurement
21. Usability Measurement

EN: Measuring usability using specific metrics.
中: 使用特定指标衡量系统可用性。
Example: Measure task time / 测量任务时间

22. Why Measure Usability?

EN: Provides objective data for evaluation and improvement.
中: 提供客观数据用于评估和改进。
Example: Compare usability scores / 比较可用性分数

23. Usability Metrics

EN: Quantifiable measures of usability.
中: 可用性相关的量化指标。
Example: Error rate / 错误率

24. Effectiveness

EN: Accuracy and completeness of task completion.
中: 任务完成的准确性和完整性。
Example: Correct submission / 正确提交

25. Efficiency

EN: Resources used to achieve goals.
中: 完成目标所用的时间与精力。
Example: Completion time / 完成时间

26. Satisfaction

EN: Users’ comfort and positive feelings.
中: 用户的舒适感和正面感受。
Example: Satisfaction survey / 满意度调查

27. Learnability

EN: Ease for new users to learn the system.
中: 新用户学习系统的容易程度。
Example: First-use success / 首次使用成功

28. Error Rate

EN: Number and severity of errors.
中: 错误的数量与严重性。
Example: Mistake count / 错误次数

29. Time on Task

EN: Time required to complete a task.
中: 完成任务所需时间。
Example: Seconds per task / 每任务秒数

30. User Satisfaction Questionnaires

EN: Collect subjective feedback from users.
中: 收集用户主观反馈。
Example: Post-test survey / 测试后问卷

31. System Usability Scale (SUS)

EN: A standardized 10-item usability questionnaire.
中: 标准化的 10 题可用性问卷。
Example: SUS score / SUS 分数

32. Quantitative and Qualitative Measures

Quantitative: Numerical data / 数字数据
Qualitative: Descriptive data / 描述性数据
Example: Time vs comments / 时间 vs 评论

33. Objective and Subjective Measures

Objective: Observable facts / 客观事实
Subjective: User opinions / 用户意见
Example: Error count vs rating / 错误数 vs 评分

34. Interpreting Usability Data

EN: Analyze results to identify problems and improvements.
中: 分析数据以发现问题并改进系统。
Example: Redesign slow workflow / 改进慢流程
